cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PL 

This paper belongs to the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category as it discusses cache attacks and their detection mechanisms. It could also belong to software engineering (cs.SE) as it proposes a new attack technique. Distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) could also be a possible sub-category as the paper discusses a cross-core covert channel. Architecture (cs.AR) and programming languages (cs.PL) could also be relevant sub-categories as the paper discusses the execution time of the flush instruction and its impact on the cache.
